1 ALIAS~
Syntax: alias
Syntax: alias <keyword>
Syntax: alias <keyword> <command phrase>
Syntax: unalias <keyword>
ALIAS by itself will give you a list of the aliases you have set. It will also
tell you how many aliases you have set out of the maximum total.
ALIAS <keyword> will show you what alias you have set does.
ALIAS <keyword> <command phrase> will create an alias to do <command phrase>
when you type <keyword>. If an alias already exists for <keyword> then it
will be replaced.
UNALIAS <keyword> will remove an alias that you have set.
Your aliases are saved with your character when you leave the game and will
be loaded when you come back.
Within your aliases you can use tokens, which start with a % for parameters.
The tokens which have an effect are %%, which just puts a % in the alias, %0,
which contains all the parameters you typed on the command line, and %1 through
%9 which contain the first 9 parameters passed on the command line. If you give
a parameter which was not passed, it will be blank when the alias is used.
For instance, if a player typed:
 > alias askabout tell %1 what do you think of %2?
Then typed:
 > askabout Zanna Galadrail
The mud would execute:
 > tell Zanna what do you think of Galadrail?
In this case, %0 would contain 'Zanna Galadrail', %1 would contain 'Zanna'
, %2 would contain 'Galadrail', and %3 through %9 would be blank./l
~

