51 BLEVELS 'builder levels' 'builder guidelines'~
BUILDER LEVEL GUIDELINES


LEVEL - 51
----------

        Evaluation period. You must begin work on your area. This includes
        creating all of your rooms and linking them. You must submit the
        idea for your area to Thallin and Beowolf for approval. Once you
        are given the go ahead by either of them you are to begin editing
        your rooms using goto vnum, where vnum is the assigned range of
        vnums given to you. Once you complete your rooms with everything
        you want them to be, ie, descriptions and valid directions please
        post a note in room 1202 on the builder board. You will need
        to say that you are done with your rooms and are requesting to
        have your area checked over. Once this is completed an immortal
        will go to your area and review it. He or she will then post a
        note on the builder board and let you know its been approved or
        if you need to make improvements. Once its been approved you will
        be advanced to the next level.

LEVEL - 52
----------

        This is the standard builder level. Builders with this level have
        the ability to create rooms, objects, mobs, and complete their
        area. At this level you are required to go through your area
        and finish it making mobs in the appropriate rooms and equiping
        the mobiles. Once you are done please post a note in room 1202
        saying that your area is complete. If you would like to learn 
        about roomprogs, objprogs, and mobprogs and how to code them you
        will need to pick up a copy of the prog doc off the web page
        and read it and understand it. Once you are done you will be
        required to submit working examples via email to beowolf@tsr.org
        for approval. If approved you may advance to master builder
        (level 53) where you will be allowed to create the progs for
        your area. If you are happy with your area and would rather not
        mess with progs then that is fine. All you need to do is post
        a note saying you would like to build another area. And start
        the basic process over, execpt you will remain at this level.
        Or you may choose to retire.

LEVEL - 53
----------

        Master Builder. You now have Roomprogs, Objectprogs, and Mobprogs
        at your disposal. You must display fluent coding abilities to
        be at this level since you may damage the mud if you mess up.
        Please take your time when creating progs for your area. If you
        remain at this level for more than 3 months and create at least
        4 unique areas and display that you would make a good immortal
        then you will be promoted accordingly. To get an immortal
        please be sure you meet the above requirements and then post
        a note on the Builder board in 1202 stating your desire and
        list your accomplishments on the MUD.
~

