51 BRULES 'builder rules'~
RULES FOR THE BUILDERS OF TSR


1)  Please do not use your character to role-play with the players
    of the MUD. This includes using the gossip channel. You should
    NOT use this channel for any reason. You may however chat when
    your taking a break on the ooc channel.

2)  You should use the avtalk channel for ALL questions regarding
    building your area. All characters with the ] after their name
    (ie. Rahvan] ) are builders. All Characters with the : after their
    name (ie. Beowolf: ) are immortals.

3)  You must show that you want to be a builder to keep your builder
    status. If you do not work on your area for a period of one month
    while creating your first area, you will be assumed MIA and be
    promptly deleted.

4)  If you have completed one area and do not show intrest in building 
    another area you will be considered retired and be placed as a 
    retired builder.

5)  Please do NOT use goto OTHER than to build your area or stay in the
    vnum range of 1200-1299. If you are caught using goto to explore
    current areas or going to mortals you will be deleted. You may
    however, if asked by another builder or immortal check out thier
    area, but ONLY if asked by them. So basically stay in your assigned
    vnum range or the 1200-1299 vnum range and no where else.

6)  You may NOT run any quests or interfere with any roleplaying in the
    MUD. Your job is to create fun and unique areas not to play.

7)  You may have mortal characters who play the MUD. However using your
    builder character to give them special items is against the rules and
    you will be deleted for breaking this rule.

8)  You room descriptions should be a min. of 4 lines long. Try and use
    proper English and spelling. Room descriptions with dialog are NOT
    acceptable. Also room descriptions that contain things such as you
    think, or you wonder, or in general the word "you" are not acceptable.
    However there are exeptions to this but these are rare. Be as 
    descriptive as possible. Make the person who is reading the descript
    see what your seeing in your mind. If you get stuck think of these
    things: what do you see? What does it smell like in the room? What is
    the floor like? Anything special ever happen in this room? Are there
    hidden things in this room and if so what might be the clue to finding
    it?

9)  ALL objects should have a PLUS and a MINUS to them. So have a reason
    for people to wear the eq, but at the same time have a reason that
    the eq might suck. So if the item adds 100 hp to the char it might
    subtract 100 mana from them or take away 2 str. We are striving for
    balanced equipment here.

10) TITLES. You have the power to set your own title. Please do NOT set
    your title to something to the effect of is sad today. or anything
    cheesy. The best title would reflect something that has to do with
    your area. Example: Beowolf is building the Halls of Chaos.

11) Do NOT give out ANY information to the players of the MUD pertaining to
    areas, levels, or any information that the mortal would not normally
    have. 

Failure to comply by any of the above rules will result in some form of 
punishment up to deletion if we feel it is appropriate.
~

