65 IMCNOTES~
Notes (boards, mail, etc) are very mud-dependent, but in general, if they
have been connected to IMC, then you can simply write notes to player@mudname
in addition to normal 'player'.
For example, you may be able to do:
note to abcde@somemud anotherplayer immortal@someothermud
and the note would go to:
  abcde on the mud called 'somemud'
  anotherplayer on your mud
  all immortals on the mud called 'someothermud'
The 'playernames' used are interpreted by the mud that receives them, not
your mud, so be careful when writing notes to group names such as 'immortal'.
If your note cannot be delivered within 12 hours for some reason (if the
mud is down, does not exist, or refused your mail) then you will get a note
from the system telling you so.
See also: IMC
~

54 IMMLEVELS 'IMM LEVELS'~
HOW TO GET THAT NEXT IMM LEVEL

LEVEL - 54
----------
     Evaluation period. You must stay active for at least 30 days in the 
     MUD. This means but is not limited to 1 Quest every 2 weeks, Doing 
     things asked of you by Beowolf or the exitsting heiarchy,  writing up 
     a valid history for yourself and having it approved by Variant, 
     staying wizi without ANY contact whatsoever with ANY of the mortals 
     for a period of  at least 1 week. Once this is done, You will 
     played into the MUD and a letter will be written stating that you 
     are allowed to go visable.  If all this is complete and the 30 days 
     is up then you will be evaluated by the existing immortal staff and 
     voted on for promotion.

LEVEL - 55
----------

     Your main purpose for this level is to role-play with the mortals. You 
     must do this for at least another 30 days.  Another aspect of this 
     level is to begin to enforce all rules. Memorize the rules, find and 
     locate bugs within the MUD, run 1 Quest every 2 weeks, and be sure 
     to unwizi and personally greet EVERY newbie (level 1) that Enters 
     the MUD. Make them feel welcome and let them  know that if they need 
     anything within reason that you will do your best to help them. If you 
     complete all this please post a note on the immortal board in room 
     1200,  AFTER 30 days saying that you feel that you are ready for 
     promotion. Please be sure to include a list of deeds that you have 
     accomplished. Once this is done you will be voted on for promotion.

LEVEL - 56
----------

      You must continue to do your best to do everything that a level 55 is 
      required to do. You now have a big task in front of you. Try and 
      spice up certain areas by adding roomprograms, mobprograms, or 
      object programs. If you do not wish to try this then you must at 
      least complete 1 area. (50 rooms at least) Continue to role-play 
      and keep an eye on things. After another 30 days please follow the 
      same procedure that you did to obtain this level. (ie. post a note)

LEVEL - 57
----------

      Continue to do everything from the previous levels. Now the main thing 
      you need to concentrate on is a HUGE quest involving yourself and 
      as many of the mortals as you can get to participate. You must 
      give the mortals at least 1 week in prepration for this event. It must 
      be so big that it will affect the mythos of the MUD.  You will also 
      need to start planning for your sect or demi-sect  depending on how 
      many sects the MUD currently has.  Start thinking about how your sect 
      will come into power, think out a story and submit it to Variant. 
      Also start constuction of your sect or demi-sect area. Once this is 
      complete please post a note on the Immortal Board again.

LEVEL - 58
----------

       Your now ready for sect or demi-sect options.  Please learn the new 
       commands at your disposure. continue to guide the mortals but now 
       help lower level immortals with questions or problems. You now 
       receive one vote for all voting options. Also you may now help us pay 
       for the site if you so feel to desire. By helping us pay for the 
       site you will receive one extra vote. So instead of your  vote 
       counting for 1 it counts as 2. Please post a note on the Immortal 
       Board if you would like to help pay for the site. Basically you  
       need to establish your sect or demi-sect by role-playing your ass 
       off, so no extra work is required. In fact you do not even have to 
       run a Quest at this level unless you really want to. After 30 days 
       post a note on the Admin Board  in 1201 for promotion.

LEVEL - 59
----------

       Now that your sect or demi-sect is established you must do everything 
       above, including Quests again. Promote role-playing and the rules 
       of the MUD. You must also do your best to advertise for the MUD.
       This means but is not limited to, posting notes on the newsgroups 
       (rec.games.mud.diku, alt.mud, and rec.games.mud.admin) Next you 
       must create a intense area for the mud using a very complex area
       consisting of mobprogs, roomprogs, and objprogs. You must also 
       continue to vote on important matters. Find bugs in areas and you 
       may also opt to help Beowolf code if you would like to learn.
       In order for you to help Beowolf you must learn the C language on 
       your own first. Once this is done simply post a note to him 
