54 IRULES 'commandments' 'immortal rules' 'beo's law' ~
THE IMMORTAL RULES OF TSR
			       'Beo's LAW'

1.)  Please respect the hierarchy of the realms. This means that if a 
     immortal of a higher level asks you to do something then do it. 

2.)  DO NOT kill mortals for the fun of it. This includes transferring 
     aggressive mobs to players. The ONLY exception to this rule is if 
     a mortal is disrespecting you by OOC: calling you names.

3.)  Please use AUTHORIZATION with care. Do NOT let any names in the MUD 
     that do not reflect the role-playing environment. This includes, but 
     is not limited to names such as Ladybug, JuJuFruit, Beavis, Buttmonkey, 
     and names that contain graphical words found in 'R' rated movies.

4.)  Do not give out information such as directions to areas, stats of 
     other players, the location of a player, or the level of another 
     player to mortals.

5.)  Do NOT raise stats, or change any of the players information 
     (ie. gold or trains) unless you are doing so for a reward for 
     a BIG QUEST.

6.)  Do not load eq for players unless there has been a crash and that 
     mortal needs reimbed. If this is the case load only a max. of 5 
     items for that player and place a note on the immortal board 
     saying whom you restored and what time it was.

7.)  Do not give out EQ unless its for a quest prize or for testing an 
     area. If you do give out an item for testing an area please make 
     sure to get it back when you are done.

8.)  You may NOT get into an OOC argument on the open channels that 
     mortals can hear. If you disagree about something please argue 
     with each other on the immortal channel. If the immortal that 
     you are arguing with is a higher level than you are, then the 
     higher level will get his or her way. If you feel that they were 
     wrong for their judgment call please note to Beowolf. However, 
     if its simply too silly I will not hesitate to demote you a level. 
     There is no need for immortals to argue over things.

9.)  If you see a player that is getting WAY out of control with you 
     please try to capture the argument or LOG it if you have the 
     log command. If you capture it please submit a copy to beowolf@tsr.org

10.) You should follow everything you need to do in help immlevels.

11.) You should always present a UNITED front to the mortals. They look 
     to us for support and guidance and if we falter they will walk all 
     over us.

12.) Please, try not to cheat with your mortal characters!!! I really 
     hate seeing this happen. If your going to play here with a mortal 
     at least try to do it the right way. You will NOT have any special 
     privileges and will be treated by the same laws that govern the 
     mortals. If you get pissed at another mortal for something don't go 
     getting all pissed off and bringing your god on, or saying, well 
     I'm a god here and you suck. or anything to that nature. I know 
     this happened when we were running the other code, but I want things 
     to be run as they should here. So basically DON'T cheat with your 
     mortal!!!

13) If a player gets out of control then put them in HELL. Use that hell 
    command and place a note on the immortal board stating how long that 
    player should be in there. PLEASE be sure to note it!!! 

14) Joking around on the imm channel - Please be careful when joking around 
    on the immortal channel. Remember that builders also get this channel. 
    So if you want to make it personal and joke around use a tell or if 
    your level 60 or higher use the ADMIN channel. However just joking 
    around with each other is perfectly fine, its not however when you 
    use personal things that the other immortal does not want every imm 
    to know.

RULES FOR SECT AND DEMI SECT GODS AND GODDESSES.

15) Do NOT go overboard with it. This means being a complete ass about 
    your actions. All the other immortals should know what your planning 
    inside your sect so that we can work as a team to make an excellent 
    story for the players.  

16) Follow the guidelines for creating a sect or demi-sect area found in 
    help sectarea.
 
17) Failure to comply by ANY of these rules includes but is not limited 
    to: First offense is a warning. Second offense is demotion. Third 
    is another demotion until you reach level 54 and if you break it 
    again you will be deleted. Also once you get demoted you have to 
    start all over with what it says you have to do in help immlevels 
    regardless of what you got done up to that point.

18) ALL of these rules are subject to change at ANY time by Beowolf 
    without warning or reason. Please walk safely and carry your slay 
    command with hopes of finding an out of control mortal. 
